{"type":"message","id":"9e583735","parentId":"80e2eb24","timestamp":"2026-05-12T15:17:22.931Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good - the database exists and has the data. The MarketData table has the right schema. The issue is that the scanner was returning \"無資料\" - no data found for ANY stocks. Let me check what's happening with the scan_universe.json output.\n\nActually, looking at the scanner code more carefully, I see it tries to run `scan_universe(ALL_STOCKS)` and then `get_top_picks(df, 10)`. The \"無資料\" message means `len(df) == 0` which means ALL stocks returned `None` from `analyze()`. \n\nWait - it printed \"已掃描 80/96...\" so it did scan. But then printed \"無資料\". \n\nSo if `len(df) == 0` after scanning 87 stocks successfully, that means every single `analyze()` call returned `None`. I need to trace through the `analyze()` function - it's checking if the dataframe is empty or has fewer than 30 rows, and also handling cases where the column names are multi-level tuples from the yfinance download.\n\nWhen I look at the output more carefully, the stock scanner results printed first (with the HTTP 404 errors for specific stocks), then the nana scanner started. The \"無資料\" error at the very end suggests the pandas DataFrame is empty even though the scan completed. This could be a working directory issue - the script is likely saving results relative to where it's executed from rather than the script's location. I'm also noticing the \"HTTP Error 404\" appears before the \"Nana Top100 Scanner\" output, which suggests these errors might be coming from a different execution context or a previous run.\n\nLooking at the command itself, I ran the script from the Ray agent directory using an absolute path, but the script has file write operations that depend on the current working directory. If the working directory wasn't set correctly, the scan_universe.json file would be written to the wrong location. Let me trace through the actual execution flow - there were HTTP errors initially, then the scan started, so I need to figure out whether this is a path resolution issue or if the yfinance download is failing for a different reason.\n\nThe \"無資料\" error message is what triggers when the DataFrame is empty, which could mean either no stocks passed the filter conditions, or the results file wasn't created properly. Let me check what scan_universe.json actually contains.\n","thinkingSignature":"de1476f1328c4726f9a24fde77ea5bf7a9f9a43b5a0bb394792c0c1deda51f5a"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_qw3o3f1m1jlw_1","name":"read","arguments":{"limit":20,"path":"C:\\Users\\USER\\.openclaw\\workspace\\Tina_Quant_System\\teams\\nana\\scan_universe.json"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":338,"output":552,"cacheRead":150848,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":151738,"cost":{"input":0.0001014,"output":0.0006624,"cacheRead":0.009050879999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00981468}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778599026740,"responseId":"06527774c403bf662b9631364d618d3f"}}
