{"type":"message","id":"9f57bbb6","parentId":"3fbf9137","timestamp":"2026-05-12T15:49:21.446Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Jo wants option B - integrate the UI elements from the new v3.1 into the existing script while keeping all the existing functionality (Shioaji, institutional data, full stock pool).\n\nThe UI elements from the v3.1 txt are:\n1. CSS styling (metric-card class + button styles)\n2. Sidebar with filters (market_choice, grade_filter, min_score)\n3. Market overview metrics at top (m1, m2, m3, m4 columns)\n4. st.tabs layout (tab_scan, tab_deep)\n5. st.toast notifications\n6. metric-card HTML for individual stock analysis\n\n\n7. st.column_config for dataframes\n\nNow I'm looking at the existing streamlit_tw_stock.py structure - it uses tabs for Taiwan and US markets starting around line 1411, with Market Overview metrics following at line 1413, and a tab structure further down at line 1418, with dataframes configured around line 1711. I need to understand how these existing elements map to the new UI components so I can properly integrate them without breaking the current functionality.\n\nThe main challenge is figuring out where to place the sidebar filters and how to restructure the layout to match the v3.1 design. Let me check the full structure of the current script to see where I can add the sidebar and how the content sections are organized.","thinkingSignature":"ecf143290911a39e6ea7b596204b12de4bb219c50ad9684d972db170018881f6"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_k855wn663v43_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"$lines = Get-Content \"C:\\Users\\USER\\.openclaw\\workspace\\Tina_Quant_System\\streamlit_tw_stock.py\"; $lines | ForEach-Object { \"$($lines.IndexOf($_)+1): $_\" } | Select-Object -First 100","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1222,"output":370,"cacheRead":84544,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":86136,"cost":{"input":0.000