{"type":"message","id":"a100aab3","parentId":"582f768e","timestamp":"2026-05-12T16:00:40.853Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The problem is that the dataframe content (column_config dict) was at 16 spaces indent BEFORE my fix. When I added 8 spaces to the st.dataframe line (from 0 to 8), the relative indentation of the contents (df, column_config={, etc.) became wrong.\n\nBefore my fix:\n- st.dataframe( = 0 spaces\n- df, = 12 spaces\n- column_config={ = 12 spaces\n- \"Score\": ... = 16 spaces\n- ... = 16 spaces\n- }, = 12 spaces\n- use_container_width=True, = 12 spaces\n\n\n- hide_index=True, = 12 spaces\n- ) = 8 spaces\n\nBut when I added 8 spaces to the opening line, the contents ended up at 20 spaces instead of the 20 they should be at relative to the 8-space base—that's actually correct. The real problem is the closing parenthesis is now at 16 spaces when it should match the 8-space indent of the opening line.\n\nWait, I'm seeing the issue now. If the opening st.dataframe is at 8 spaces and the closing ) is at 16 spaces, that's inconsistent—they should both be at 8. Let me trace back through what the indentation actually was before my fix to understand where the mismatch started. So after shifting everything, the closing parenthesis would land at 16 spaces, but the error persists at line 1732. The problem might be that my indentation shift was applied to the wrong block—the one inside the for loop instead of the outer dataframe structure. I need to reconsider whether the entire dataframe construct should have been shifted or just a specific part of it. the problem is that `st.dataframe(...)` at 8 spaces is followed by content at 20 spaces, but then the closing `)` is only at 16 spaces—that's inconsistent and invalid Python syntax.\n\nThe fix should shift `df = pd.DataFrame(rows)` from 8 to 0 spaces so it aligns with the dataframe call, and move the closing `)` up to match the opening parenthesis at 8 spaces. Then `grade_filter` would go back to 12 spaces as part of the expander block. I should revert all the dataframe indentation and apply the corrections properly instead of making incremental changes.","thinkingSignature":"07f2b890c2e8d736b025fbf45c4f2ea1596e1dbc4836ac940ad1d6fbc6435185"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_rrqlpsr2bvab_1","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"path = r\"C:\\Users\\USER\\.openclaw\\workspace\\Tina_Quant_System\\streamlit_tw_stock.py\"\nwith open(path, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n    lines = f.readlines()\n\n# Current state (from fix_streamlit_indent.py):\n# st.dataframe( at 8 spaces\n# df at 20 spaces, column_config at 20 spaces, dict content at 24 spaces\n# closing ) at 16 spaces\n# with st.expander at 12 spaces\n# grade_filter at 12 spaces\n\n# The issue: st.dataframe call should be at 8 (inside 'if filtered:' block at 4, +4 = 8)\n# But the dict content is at 24 (was 16 before fix, +8 = 24) \n# closing ) at 16 (was 8 before fix, +8 = 16)\n# grade_filter should be at 12 (same level as rows = [] and for loop)\n\n# The CORRECT structure:\n# 'if filtered:' at 4\n# 'rows = []' at 8\n# 'for r in filtered:' at 8\n# 'inst = ...' at 12\n# ... (loop body)\n# 'df = pd.DataFrame(rows)' at 8  <-- inside 'if filtered:', same level as rows = []\n# 'st.dataframe(df, ...)' at 8   <-- inside 'if filtered:'\n#   'df,' at 12\n#   'column_config={', at 12\n#     dict items at 16\n#   '},' at 12\n#   'use_container_width=True,' at 12\n#   'hide_index=True,' at 12\n# ')' at 8\n# 'with st.expander(\"Send to Telegram\"):' at 8\n# 'grade_filter = ...' at 12\n\n# Current WRONG state:\n# st.dataframe( at 8\n# df, at 20\n# column_config={ at 20\n# dict items at 24\n# }, at 20\n# use_container_width at 20\n# hide_index at 20\n# ) at 16\n# with st.expander at 12\n# grade_filter at 12\n\n# Fix: shift st.dataframe+df from 8 to 0, shift contents from 20/24 to 12/16, shift ) from 16 to 8, shift expander from 12 to 8\n# Basically shift the whole st.dataframe block back by 8\n\n# Line 1712: st.dataframe( = 8 -> 0\n# Line 1713: df, = 20 -> 12\n# Line 1714: column_config={ = 20 -> 12\n# Line 1715-1724: dict items = 24 -> 16\n# Line 1725: }, = 20 -> 12\n# Line 1726: use_container = 20 -> 12\n# Line 1727: hide_index = 20 -> 12\n# Line 1728: ) = 16 -> 8\n# Line 1732: with st.expander = 12 -> 8\n# Line 1734: grade_filter = 12 (correct)\n\n# Apply fixes\nfor i in range(1711, min(1735, len(lines))):\n    l = lines[i]\n    if not l.strip():\n        continue\n    current_indent = len(l) - len(l.lstrip())\n    \n    if i == 1711:  # st.dataframe(\n        lines[i] = l.lstrip()  # remove all indent\n        print(f\"Line {i+1}: st.dataframe( -> 0 spaces\")\n    elif i == 1712:  # df,\n        lines[i] = '            ' + l.lstrip()  # 12 spaces\n    elif i in range(1713, 1725):  # column_config and dict items\n        lines[i] = '                ' + l.lstrip()  # 16 spaces\n    elif i == 1725:  # },\n        lines[i] = '            ' + l.lstrip()  # 12 spaces\n    elif i in [1726, 1727]:  # use_container, hide_index\n        lines[i] = '            ' + l.lstrip()  # 12 spaces\n    elif i == 1728:  # )\n        lines[i] = '        ' + l.lstrip()  # 8 spaces\n    elif i == 1732:  # with st.expander\n        lines[i] = '        ' + l.lstrip()  # 8 spaces\n        print(f\"Line {i+1}: with st.expander -> 8 spaces\")\n\nwith open(path, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n    f.writelines(lines)\n\n# Verify\nimport ast\nwith open(path, encoding='utf-8') as f:\n    src = f.read()\ntry:\n    ast.parse(src)\n    print(\"Syntax OK\")\nexcept SyntaxError as e:\n    print(f\"SyntaxError: line {e.lineno}: {e.msg}\")\n    lines2 = src.split('\\n')\n    for i in range(max(0, e.lineno-3), min(len(lines2), e.lineno+2)):\n        print(f\"{i+1}: {lines2[i]}\")\n","path":"C:\\Users\\USER\\.openclaw\\agents\\ray\\fix_streamlit_indent.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":505,"output":1677,"cacheRead":135264,"cacheWrite