{"type":"message","id":"052eca16","parentId":"39822e24","timestamp":"2026-05-12T16:01:31.383Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the real problem clearly! \n\n```\n1708 [12]: })          ← rows.append dict closes, inside for loop (correct)\n1709 [BLANK]\n1710 [ 8]: df = pd.DataFrame(rows)   ← inside 'if filtered:' (correct)\n1711 [BLANK]\n1712 [ 0]: st.dataframe(    ← WRONG! at column 0, should be 8 (inside 'if filtered:')\n```\n\nThe `st.dataframe(` call starts at column 0, but it should be indented 8 spaces to be inside the `if filtered:` block (which is at 4 spaces).\n\nAll the st.dataframe content lines are then at 12/16 (relative to where they should be - they need an extra 8 spaces).\n\nThe fix:\n- st.dataframe( at 0 → 8\n\n\n- df, at 12 → 20\n- column_config={ at 16 → 24\n- dict items at 16 → 24\n- }, at 16 → 24 (but this is wrong - it should match column_config)\n- Actually wait: column_config dict is a NESTED dict inside the function call. The whole st.dataframe() call including column_config={} needs to be at indent 8. The dict items inside column_config should be at 16.\n\nSo the correct structure is:\n- st.dataframe( at 8\n  - df, at 12 (argument to function)\n  - column_config={ at 12 (argument to function)\n    - dict items at 16\n  - }, at 12\n  - use_container_width=True, at 12\n  - hide_index=True, at 12\n- ) at 8\n\nCurrently the code is off by 8 spaces across all these lines. Let me write another fix script to correct this indentation issue.","thinkingSignature":"5668d0e1dedc213450c6c6aed7db03c98ecc599f6fc66e0dc3a96aec24a628d9"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_p0tyo6zphrfn_1","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"path = r\"C:\\Users\\USER\\.openclaw\\workspace\\Tina_Quant_System\\streamlit_tw_stock.py\"\nwith open(path, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n    lines = f.readlines()\n\n# st.dataframe() is at column 0 but should be at 8 (inside 'if filtered:')\n# All content is misaligned by 8 spaces\n\n# Correct structure:\n# st.dataframe( at 8\n#   df, at 12\n#   column_config={ at 12\n#     dict items at 16\n#   }, at 12\n#   use_container_width=True, at 12\n#   hide_index=True, at 12\n# ) at 8\n\n# Line 1712 (index 1711): st.dataframe( = 0 → 8\n# Line 1713 (index 1712): df, = 12 → 20\n# Line 1714 (index 1713): column_config={ = 16 → 24\n# Lines 1715-1724 (index 1714-1723): dict items = 16 → 24\n# Line 1725 (index 1724): }, = 16 → 24 (WRONG - should be 12! The } closes column_config={, not st.dataframe()\n# Ah wait - column_config={ starts at 24, and its dict closes at line 1725 which is 24... \n# But if column_config starts at 24, the } closing it should be at the SAME indent as column_config={\n# Let me re-check...\n\n# Looking at the output again:\n# 1714 [16]: column_config={\n# 1715 [16]: \"Score\": ...\n# ...all dict items at 16...\n# 1725 [16]: },\n# 1726 [12]: use_container_width=True,\n# 1727 [12]: hide_index=True,\n# 1728 [12]: )\n\n# column_config={ is at 16\n# Its dict items are at 16 (same indent = wrong! they should be at 20)\n# The }, is at 16 (same indent = wrong! it should be at 16 to close the dict)\n# use_container_width at 12 (should be 12 = correct, same level as column_config={ argument)\n\n# Actually looking more carefully:\n# The line \"column_config={\" starts at 16 (correct for a function argument at indent 12)\n# The dict items inside should be at 20 (not 16!)\n# The \"},\" closing the dict should be at 16 (same as column_config={)\n# use_container_width at 12 is correct\n# ) at 12 is wrong - should be 8\n\n# Fix needed:\n# st.dataframe( at 8\n# df, at 20\n# column_config={ at 24  \n# dict items at 20\n# }, at 24\n# use_container_width at 20\n# hide_index at 20\n# ) at 8\n\n# Wait, but column_config is an ARGUMENT to st.dataframe(), so it should be at indent 12 (one level deeper)\n# And its dict items at 16 (two levels deeper)\n# Closing } at 12 (back to column_config level)\n# use_container_width at 12 (still inside st.dataframe call)\n# hide_index at 12\n# ) at 8\n\n# Currently:\n# st.dataframe( at 0 → 8\n# df, at 12 → 20\n# column_config={ at 16 → 24\n# dict items at 16 → 20  \n# }, at 16 → 24\n# use_container at 12 → 20\n# hide_index at 12 → 20\n# ) at 12 → 8\n\n# But there's another issue: \"column_config={\" is a function ARGUMENT\n# In Python, arguments at the opening parenthesis continue on the next line\n# If st.dataframe( is at 8, and the first argument \"df,\" is on next line, it should be at 12\n# But \"df,\" is currently at 12 - that's correct!\n# And \"column_config={\" is the second argument, so it should also be at 12\n# Currently it's at 16 - that's 4 too many!\n\n# OK so the REAL correct is:\n# st.dataframe( at 8\n#   df, at 12\n#   column_config={ at 12  (second arg)\n#     dict items at 16\n#   }, at 12  (close the dict)\n#   use_container_width=True, at 12\n#   hide_index=True, at 12\n# ) at 8\n\n# Current:\n# st.dataframe( at 0\n#   df, at 12\n#   column_config={ at 16\n#     dict items at 16 (wrong! should be 20)\n#   }, at 16\n#   use_container at 12\n#   hide_index at 12\n#   ) at 12\n\n# OK let me just fix this programmatically by reading the current indent and applying correct fix\n","path":"C:\\Users\\USER\\.openclaw\\agents\\ray\\fix_streamlit_indent.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1900,"output":1531,"cacheRead":137696,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":141127,"cost":{"input":0.00057,"output":0.0018372,"cacheRead":0.00826176,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.01066896}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778601656439,"responseId":"065281bbae910a0dbf003a410876545d"}}
