{"type":"message","id":"cb0555f2","parentId":"7be5f551","timestamp":"2026-05-12T17:02:57.180Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting! The model is outputting a \"Thinking Process:\" block. This suggests that:1. The SYSTEM prompt in the Modelfile is influencing the model's output format\n2. The model is trying to follow the \"think about your reasoning\" pattern which might be baked into the base Qwen3.5 model\n3. The model IS working, but the output includes \"Thinking Process:\" which might be from a Qwen3.5-inherent chain-of-thought feature\n\nLet me try with `thinking: false` parameter if Ollama supports it, or try to use the chat API instead.\n\nActually, looking at the response - the model IS generating output, which means it IS functional! The issue is that it includes \"Thinking Process:\" in the output. This might be because:\n\n\n- Qwen3.5 has a built-in thinking mode that's enabled by default\n- The SYSTEM prompt isn't properly suppressing it\n- There's a mismatch between the `stop` parameter in the Modelfile and what the model actually outputs\n\nLet me try the chat endpoint instead to see if that helps control the output format better.\n","thinkingSignature":"b63a762ed0772dea95942e240a789b2f860488d0f56b12654a65a35aba10f0dd"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_fe8w2jgxw98k_1","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"import requests, json, time\n\nprint(\"=== Ray-v3.5 Live Test ===\")\n\n# Try chat endpoint instead of generate\nmessages = [\n    {\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": \"You are Ray Commander. Respond ONLY with JSON. No thinking. No explanation. Format: {\\\"commander\\\":\\\"ray-v3.5\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"online\\\"}\"},\n    {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"status check\"}\n]\n\nprint(\"\\n[Test 1] Chat API with system prompt override\")\nstart = time.time()\ntry:\n    resp = requests.post('http://localhost:11434/api/chat', json={\n        'model': 'ray-v3.5',\n        'messages': messages,\n        'stream': False,\n        'options': {\n            'temperature': 0.3,\n            'num_predict': 80,\n            'stop': ['```', 'Thinking Process:', '\\n']\n        }\n    }, timeout=30)\n    elapsed = time.time() - start\n    content = resp.json().get('message', {}).get('content', '')\n    print(f\"  Time: {elapsed:.1f}s\")\n    print(f\"  Content: {content[:200]}\")\nexcept Exception as e:\n    print(f\"  FAIL: {e}\")\n\n# Try without stop tokens\nprint(\"\\n[Test 2] Generate with raw prompt (no system)\")\nstart = time.time()\ntry:\n    resp = requests.post('http://localhost:11434/api/generate', json={\n        'model': 'ray-v3.5',\n        'prompt': '1+1=2. Respond JSON: {\\\"answer\\\":2}',\n        'stream': False,\n        'options': {'temperature': 0.3, 'num_predict': 60, 'no_truncate': True}\n    }, timeout=30)\n    elapsed = time.time() - start\n    content = resp.json().get('response', '')\n    print(f\"  Time: {elapsed:.1f}s\")\n    print(f\"  Content: {content[:150]}\")\nexcept Exception as e:\n    print(f\"  FAIL: {e}\")\n\nprint(\"\\nDone\")","path":"C:\\Users\\USER\\.openclaw\\agents\\ray\\test_ray_v35.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":283,"output":727,"cacheRead":71488,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":72498,"cost":{"input":0.00008489999999999999,"output":0.0008724,"cacheRead":0.0042892799999999995,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.005246579999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778605361319,"responseId":"06529034af4814e0f6f33bb54e24a7ee"}}
