{"type":"message","id":"c5556171","parentId":"dd3c3994","timestamp":"2026-05-12T17:03:16.581Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is clear now! When `ray-v3.5` was created, it was created FROM `qwen3.5-4b-iq4xs` which uses the Qwen3.5-4B base model that has a built-in thinking/reasoning mode. The model is producing \"\" thinking tags as its response, which means the system prompt or the base model's instruction isn't working correctly.\n\nThe Modelfile I created has the `stop` tokens `[STRATEGY]` and ` ```json` but those don't stop the \"\" thinking process. I need to update the Modelfile to also stop the thinking token format.\n\nActually - wait. Looking at the test output, the model is outputting \"Thinking Process:\" content. \n\nThis is the default Qwen3.5 behavior! It's a reasoning model. To get JSON output, I need to either disable reasoning in the Modelfile with `no_reasoning: true` or similar, or find the right parameter to turn it off. Let me check what parameters Qwen3.5 supports for disabling thinking/reasoning mode.\n\nLooking at the test results, the model is outputting thinking content in JSON format but it's being truncated. The issue is the thinking tokens are being included in the response. I need to add `Thinking Process:` to the stop tokens in the Modelfile so it stops before that part. Since I can't edit the Modelfile directly after creation, I'll need to recreate the model with a new Modelfile that includes this stop token and also check what parameter disables reasoning in Qwen3.5.\n","thinkingSignature":"9285838d0ed78bc2f9df0ca5d6d72a82d6ad74e961b8fecf7e43e5170373071b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_st06g176xsq1_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ollama show ray-v3.5 --license 2>&1 | Select-Object -First 5","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":248,"output":383,"cacheRead":72256,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":72887,"cos