{"type":"message","id":"ec1e4071","parentId":"d9f5959c","timestamp":"2026-05-12T17:05:15.691Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is likely with how the Qwen3.5-4B model was created. Let me check the Modelfile we used and see if there's a problem with the SYSTEM prompt that's causing the Thinking Process to always trigger.\n\nActually, looking at the ray-v3.5 Modelfile we created, the SYSTEM prompt contains `<COMMANDER_CORE>` and `<MASTER_PROTOCOL>` tags that might be confusing Qwen3.5's built-in thinking template.\n\nQwen3.5 models have a built-in `<think>` tag behavior. The SYSTEM prompt we added has XML-like tags `<COMMANDER_CORE>`, `<MASTER_PROTOCOL>`, etc. which might be conflicting.\n \nI'm noticing a consistent pattern across both the base and ray-v3.5 models where the thinking process is always triggered regardless of the prompt format. This suggests the thinking behavior is baked into the model's configuration rather than being prompt-dependent.\n\nLooking at the Modelfile for ray-v3.5, I see the temperature setting at 0.2, but I should verify whether there's a separate configuration controlling the thinking feature itself, since Qwen3.5-4B has this enabled by default and we'd need to explicitly disable it if we want to turn it off.\n","thinkingSignature":"588378b859eea5df1921328df039f50f4bd8fac1ddc6491ed9d4832e15b46f5e"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_yk96xut4q04z_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Select-String -Path \"C:\\Users\\USER\\AppData\\Local\\Programs\\Ollama\\models\\qwen35-"},"partialJson":"{\"command\":\"Select-String -Path \\\"C:\\\\Users\\\\USER\\\\AppData\\\\Local\\\\Programs\\\\Ollama\\\\models\\\\qwen35-","index":1}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":68550,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":68550,"cost":{"input":0.020565,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.020565}},"stopReason":"stop","timesta