ally workable. The key insight is that the thinking is NOT a bug - it's a feature of Qwen3.5. We just need to handle it in post-processing.\n\nLet me summarize for Jo:\n- ray-v3.5 IS working ✅\n- It responds in 2-3 seconds ✅\n- The response includes a \"Thinking Process:\" block (Qwen3.5's built-in thinking)\n- We need to strip this block in post-processing before parsing JSON\n\nThis is actually fine for the trading system since we're extracting JSON anyway - we just need to add a cleaning step to remove the thinking block before passing the content to the JSON parser.\n\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_uat58t9nln4m_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python -c \"import requests; resp=requests.post('http://localhost:11434/api/generate', json={'model':'ray-v3.5','prompt':'Give me JSON: {status:ok}','stream':False,'options':{'num_predict':300,'temperature':0.2}}, timeout=20); r=resp.json().get('response',''); import re; clean=re.sub(r'\\<\\/?think\\>','',r); print(clean[:300])\"","timeout":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":340,"output":648,"cacheRead":78336,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":79324,"cost":{"input":0.000102,"output":0.0007775999999999999,"cacheRead":0.004700159999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00557976}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778605620924,"responseId":"06529138ef44df6e556a821b1ae52e24"}}
