{"type":"message","id":"b293493c","parentId":"ee011920","timestamp":"2026-05-12T17:08:11.216Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Ray-v3.5 is working! The model is responding with proper JSON and no thinking output. The issue is that the thinking tags (\"\",\"","thinkingSignature":"e650a58b7e3d381936e2df95cf83fc85f34233bdc8cffd453697edb2fd125c44"},{"type":"text","text":"\") are in the model's output, but the JSON portion is correct.\n\nWhen I ask for clean JSON output, I get clean JSON. The \"Thinking Process:\" in the raw output is actually the thinking tag content. So the model has thinking enabled by default.\n\nKey observations:\n1. `num_predict` of 120-200 is not enough to suppress the thinking + response\n2. With `num_predict` too low, we get truncated thinking\n3. With `num_predict` higher, we get thinking tags\n\n\n4. The `temperature: 0.3` parameter on the `generate` call is probably overriding the Modelfile's `temperature 0.2` setting\n\nI'm getting solid JSON responses from the model—it's just that the thinking block tags are cluttering the raw output. For parsing, I can filter those out easily. Now I need to check if the SYSTEM prompt is actually being respected by sending a message with instructions that reference Ray's master protocols and checking if the model's response reflects that context.\n\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_qtj5n7k6so21_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python -c \"import requests,re; resp=requests.post('http://localhost:11434/api/chat', json={'model':'ray-v3.5','messages':[{'role':'user','content':'TSLA RSI65 VIX18. JSON only {action,confidence,reason} no extra text'}],'stream':False,'options':{'num_predict':200,'temperature':0.3}}, timeout=25); msg=resp.json().get('message',{}); raw=msg.get('content',''); print('Content:', raw[:400])\"","timeout":35}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":285,"output":390,"cacheRead":7936