{"type":"message","id":"ff8ae4a3","parentId":"5eea6bce","timestamp":"2026-05-12T17:08:26.852Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, so the ray-v3.5 model IS working. It responds with JSON! The thinking tags are always prepended, but the JSON is there.\n\nThe issue is that:\n1. The model prepends `\\n\\nThinking Process:\\n...` \n2. Then the JSON response\n3. Then `","thinkingSignature":"81992d9918d8ab5635175b8e53648552f2103370890a80fe3aa503e1b40793fd"},{"type":"text","text":"`4. Sometimes more conversation history follows\n\nThis is a known behavior with Qwen3.5 - it has \"Thinking Mode\" enabled by default. We need to disable it.Options to disable thinking:- `thinking.enable: false`- `enable_thinking: false`\n- Remove the `<|im_start|>` system messages that might be enabling it\nLet me check the original qwen3.5-4b-iq4xs system prompt and see if I can create a version without thinking.Actually, I should try adding a parameter to disable thinking in the Modelfile:\n```\nPARAMETER enable_thinking false```\n\nBut wait - when I first tested `qwen3.5-4b-iq4xs` it also showed thinking tags. So the thinking is baked into the base model, not added by the Modelfile.\n\nLet me try adding `enable_thinking false` to the Modelfile and recreate.\n\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_slnhzusw2c5z_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"edits":[{"newText":"PARAMETER temperature 0.2\nPARAMETER top_p 0.85\nPARAMETER num_ctx 8192\nPARAMETER num_thread 14\nPARAMETER enable_thinking false\nPARAMETER think_depth -1","oldText":"PARAMETER temperature 0.2\nPARAMETER top_p 0.85\nPARAMETER num_ctx 8192\nPARAMETER num_thread 14"}],"path":"C:\\Users\\USER\\AppData\\Local\\Programs\\Ollama\\models\\qwen35-4b-iq4xs\\Ray-v3.5.Modelfile"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":299,"output":413,"cacheRead":79616,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":80328,"cost":{"input":0.0000897,"output":0.0004956,"cacheRead":0.004