{"type":"message","id":"b7d0a473","parentId":"e42a85db","timestamp":"2026-05-12T17:08:33.052Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait - `enable_thinking` and `think_depth` are likely not valid Ollama parameters. Qwen3.5's thinking is a system-level feature that needs to be disabled in the model config, but Ollama's Modelfile parameter naming might differ. Let me check if these are valid.\n\nActually, these are likely not valid Ollama parameters. Ollama doesn't have a native `enable_thinking` parameter. The thinking is embedded in the model's system prompt.\n\nInstead, I should modify the SYSTEM prompt to tell the model to never show its thinking process. Or I can use a different approach - configure the stop tokens.\n\n\nLet me just update the Modelfile by removing the invalid thinking parameters and rely on adjusting the system prompt instead.\n","thinkingSignature":"29be50a40bc08a0100328847a2d9f1f27597eb0d85d03b464657886e45872cd5"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_53zqbvk9pxr9_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"edits":[{"newText":"PARAMETER temperature 0.2\nPARAMETER top_p 0.85\nPARAMETER num_ctx 8192\nPARAMETER num_thread 14","oldText":"PARAMETER temperature 0.2\nPARAMETER top_p 0.85\nPARAMETER num_ctx 8192\nPARAMETER num_thread 14\nPARAMETER enable_thinking false\nPARAMETER think_depth -1"}],"path":"C:\\Users\\USER\\AppData\\Local\\Programs\\Ollama\\models\\qwen35-4b-iq4xs\\Ray-v3.5.Modelfile"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":258,"output":309,"cacheRead":79872,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":80439,"cost":{"input":0.0000774,"output":0.00037079999999999996,"cacheRead":0.004792319999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.005240519999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778605706862,"responseId":"0652918c29e7c7473aaece7c5df471d7"}}
