{"type":"message","id":"8eefb977","parentId":"3d21f326","timestamp":"2026-05-12T17:08:38.481Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me verify and test. The thinking was the issue - it was outputting thinking tags. But the JSON content IS correct and clean. I can work with this. The thinking adds latency and token overhead, but it's working.\n\nNow let me understand why it was initially returning empty content in my earlier tests. The test script was checking `resp.json().get('response', '')` in Test 1 and `msg.get('content', '')` in Test 2. But in the generate API, the thinking happens but the actual content is there too. The issue might be that when I'm streaming=False and the full response is generated, the JSON content is included but only the non-thinking part. But when I check response, it's there.\n \nI think the empty outputs in those early tests were from rate limiting and timeouts during the heavy load period when seven processes were running simultaneously. The VRAM issue with the high GPU utilization was compounding the problem. Once I freed up VRAM, responses started coming through properly.\n\nNow the model is working correctly—it's just outputting that verbose thinking process before the actual response. The JSON is clean and properly formatted, so I can move forward with testing.\n","thinkingSignature":"afe97dd3ddfff21799f5bccb896bcd0621850a08efd0342ad0af5da24b383c62"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_011rcjee1awx_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ollama list | Select-String \"ray-v3.5\"","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":281,"output":286,"cacheRead":80064,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":80631,"cost":{"input":0.0000843,"output":0.0003432,"cacheRead":0.004803839999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.005231339999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778605713066,"responseId":"06529193c053f638d152e433f0c447d7"}}
