{"type":"message","id":"4e28ef59","parentId":"8e83660f","timestamp":"2026-05-12T17:08:48.906Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"New digest: ddc2806e2c83 (previously e1efecda43da). So the model was recreated. Now the thinking is baked into the system prompt - but thinking still appears when using generate API with longer outputs. The chat API seems cleaner in its second turn.\n\nThe key issue is that the first message in the chat API shows \"...","thinkingSignature":"274550142c727b154ba6855581e70174168ba1f5cdc76e61226adb6cffc894ec"},{"type":"text","text":"\" as part of the output. This is because the model is configured to always do thinking, and the thinking content gets leaked into the output when the user message triggers a long response.\n\nFor the router to work properly with 4B, I need to ensure that:1. The system prompt gets applied correctly (it does - \"Ray-v3.5\" output)2. The thinking is contained and stripped by the router when processing responses (it currently is not)\n\nLet me update the llm_router.py to properly strip thinking blocks. But first, let me test the current state and see what the actual user experience is when the router calls the model.\n\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_51wv3u3cxozl_1","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"import requests, re, json\n\ndef call_ray_v35(market_data, top_5_memories=None):\n    \"\"\"\n    Router interface: call ray-v3.5 for trading decision\n    \"\"\"\n    prompt = f\"\"\"[Market_Data]: {market_data}\"\"\"\n    if top_5_memories:\n        prompt += f\"\\n[Historical_Memory]: {top_5_memories}\"\n    prompt += \"\\nRespond ONLY with JSON: {\\\"action\\\",\\\"confidence\\\",\\\"reason\\\"}\"\n\n    resp = requests.post('http://localhost:11434/api/chat', json={\n        'model': 'ray-v3.5',\n        'messages': [{'role': 'user', 'content': prompt}],\n        'stream': False,\n        'options': {'temperature': 0.3, 'num_predict': 200}\n    }, timeout=25)\n\n    raw = resp.json().get('message', {}).get('content', '')\n    # Strip thinking blocks\n    clean = re.sub(r'<\\|think\\|>.*?<\\|/think\\|>', '', raw, flags=re.DOTALL)\n    clean = re.sub(r'<think>.*?', '', clean, flags=re.DOTALL)\n    clean = clean.strip()\n\n    try:\n        # Extract JSON\n        if '{' in clean:\n            start = clean.index('{')\n            end = clean.rindex('}') + 1\n            return json.loads(clean[start:end])\n    except:\n        pass\n    return {'raw': clean}\n\n# Test\nresult = call_ray_v35(\"TSLA price 245 RSI 65 VIX 18\")\nprint(f\"Action: {result.get('action','?')}\")\nprint(f\"Raw output: {result.get('raw','none')[:200]}\")","path":"C:\\Users\\USER\\.openclaw\\agents\\ray\\test_router.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":111,"output":628,"cacheRead":80320,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":81059,"cost":{"input":0.000033299999999999996,"output":0.0007536,"cacheRead":0.004819199999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.005606099999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778605718748,"responseId":"065291999db3f93356b1a160d11752be"}}
